{{Italic title}} {{taxobox |image = Anisodus tanguticus1.jpg |image_caption = ''[[Anisodus tanguticus]]'' in flower |regnum = [[Plant]]ae |unranked_divisio = [[Flowering plant|Angiosperms]] |unranked_classis = [[Eudicots]] |unranked_ordo = [[Asterids]] |ordo = [[Solanales]] |familia = [[Solanaceae]] |tribus = [[Hyoscyameae]] |genus = '''''Anisodus''''' |genus_authority = [[Johann Heinrich Friedrich Link|Link]] ex [[Kurt Sprengel|Sprengel]]? |}} '''''Anisodus''''' is a genus of [[angiosperms|flowering plant]] in the family [[Solanaceae]].
==Habitat== It is native to [[China]], [[Tibet]], [[India]], [[Bhutan]], and [[Nepal]].
==Medicinal uses== One species, ''A. tanguticus'' ({{zh|c=[[wiktionary:山|山]][[wiktionary:莨|莨]][[wiktionary:菪|菪]]|p=shān làngdàng}}), is one of the [[Chinese herbology#50 fundamental herbs|50 fundamental herbs]] used in [[traditional Chinese medicine]].
