{{short description|A largely psychological doctrine that when a species is removed from the habitat in which it evolved,  it will develop maladaptive behavior}}
{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}
The '''Evolutionary Principle''' is a largely psychological doctrine which roughly states that when a [[species]] is removed from the [[Habitat (ecology)|habitat]] in which it [[evolution|evolved]], or that habitat changes significantly within a brief period (evolutionarily speaking), the species will develop maladaptive or outright [[wiktionary:pathological|pathological]] behavior. The Evolutionary Principle is important in [[Neo-Tribalism|neo-tribalist]] and [[anarcho-primitivist]] thinking.

