{{coord|40|42|44|N|111|51|25|W|type:landmark|display=title}}
The '''Midwives College of Utah''', formerly the Utah School of Midwifery, is an institution of [[Direct-entry midwife|direct-entry]] [[midwifery]] training. Founded in 1980, it is one of the largest and longest-standing direct-entry (out-of-[[hospital]]) midwifery programs in the nation. It has been accredited through the [http://www.meacschools.org/ Midwifery Education Accreditation Council] (MEAC) since 1996, which is approved by the [[U.S. Secretary of Education]] as a nationally-recognized [[accrediting agency]].  The school is also accepted by the [[California Medical Board]] for state licensure.

The college offers a [[Bachelor of Science]] in Midwifery and a [[Master of Science]] in Midwifery. Students are eligible to take the [http://www.narm.org North American Registry of Midwives] (NARM) [[exam]] upon graduation, and to receive the designation of Certified Professional Midwife (CPM).

